text: The Boholano people, (Boholanos, Bol-Anon) are one of the visayan ethnic group aside Cebuanos in Central Visayas, The Eskaya and Bol-Anons are the tribes majority in province of Bohol and it has native dialect of Boholano, It is related into the Cebuano speakers and can understand by themselves.https://dbpedia.org/page/Boholano_people The native Bol-Anon and other ancestries are from United States acrossing from Leyte Gulf in the Indo- Pacific. ==Reference== Category:Ethnic groups in the Philippines
title: Boholano people
